nodes.text: Coya Elliott is credited as an assistant voice editor for Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic, Star Wars: Jedi Knight: Mysteries of the Sith, Star Wars: Rebel Assault II: The Hidden Empire, Star Wars: Masters of Teräs Käsi, and Star Wars: Jedi Knight: Dark Forces II. She was also a dialouge editor for Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace video game, a voice editor for Star Wars Episode I: The Gungan Frontier, as well as the voice department manager for Star Wars: Rogue Squadron.

Additionally, Elliott worked on Star Wars Episode I: Racer, Star Wars: DroidWorks, Star Wars: Rogue Squadron 3D, Star Wars: Force Commander, Star Wars: Starfighter, and Star Wars: Episode I Jedi Power Battles.
Coya Elliott was the supervising assistant sound editor for Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones and the supervising assistant editor for Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith.
